==English==
===Etymology===
Coined ca. 1828 as a verb, used as a noun ca. 1904.

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɑː(r)leɪ|-ɑː(r)leɪ]]

===Transitive verb===
'''to parlay'''
# To [[carry]] [[forward]] the [[stake]] and [[winning]]s from a [[bet]] onto a [[subsequent]] [[wager]].
===Noun===
'''parlay'''
# Such a [[bet]] or series of bets.
===See also===
*[[parley]]
===Etymology 2===
Probably a variation of ''[[party]].''
===Transitive verb===
'''to parlay'''
# (''West Coast AAVE'') To [[party]].

